9:["$","section",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__section","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__container","children":[["$","div","0",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__textBlock","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__subTitle","children":"The Critical Importance of Deck Maintenance in Northern Virginia"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Residential decks in Northern Virginia are subject to extreme environmental stress. Between the high humidity of our summers and the snow and ice cycles of winter, even the best-built decks eventually require professional attention. As a leading deck builder in Loudoun County, Fairfax County, and Prince William County, Loudoun Decks understands that deck repair is not just about aesthetics-it's about preserving a critical structural component of your home."]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["We have seen countless decks in Ashburn and Leesburg that look healthy on the surface but have significant rot hidden beneath the decking boards. This is why we advocate for proactive maintenance and professional safety audits. Catching a loose ledger or a rotting post early can save you thousands of dollars in full replacement costs and prevent potentially dangerous structural failures."]}],["$","p","2",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["If you are searching for a deck contractor near you who values safety and structural integrity, look no further. Our team provides comprehensive restoration services designed specifically for the unique architectural styles and building codes found across NoVA and Stafford."]}]]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__textBlock","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__subTitle","children":"Identifying Red Flags: When Your Deck Becomes a Hazard"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Many homeowners in regions like Fairfax Station and Burke overlook the subtle signs of deck degradation. The most common 'red flag' is wobbly or loose railings. In Virginia, building codes have become much stricter regarding railing attachment methods because railings are responsible for preventing falls. If your railing posts are through-bolted rather than just nailed, you are in much better shape. If they move when you lean on them, you need immediate deck repair."]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["Another critical area is the stair system. Over time, the 'stringers' (the side supports of the stairs) can pull away from the deck or rot at the base where they touch the ground. We frequently handle stair restorations in Sterling and Herndon, reinforcing these high-traffic areas with custom steel brackets and new pressure-treated timber. Ensuring your stairs are level and secure is a top priority for any 5-Star Google Rated contractor."]}],["$","p","2",{"className":"ServiceContentExpansion-module__6_-y9q__paragraph","children":["As your custom deck builder and restoration expert, we perform deep-dive inspections to identify these hazards before they escalate into emergencies."]}]]}],"$L14"]}],"$L15","$L16"]}]}]
